sections.text:
Countries may wish to enter into agreements concerning food import and export inspection and certification systems to:
a) provide an enhanced means of assuring that exported products conform to importing country requirements;
b) eliminate duplication of activities and use collective resources more efficiently and effectively;
c) provide a mechanism for the cooperative exchange of expertise, assistance and information to help assure and enhance conformity with requirements.

